cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel approach for wireless interference identification using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves signal processing and information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of deep learning models for classification tasks indicates cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of sensing snapshots, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of wireless communication standards such as IEEE 802.11 b/g, IEEE 802.15.4 and IEEE 802.15.1, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
